# Workflow Rules

## Rule sync policy
CLAUDE.md, `.claude/rules/`, and `.cursor/rules/` must stay in sync. When you add, change, or remove a rule in one, apply the same change to the others in the same operation. If they diverge, that's a bug — fix immediately.

## Code formatting
Always run `black` after modifying a Python file. Never commit unformatted Python code.

## Package management
Use `uv install <package>` to install dependencies.

## Documentation
Always use mermaid diagrams for flows, architecture, state transitions, and relationships. Prefer a diagram over a wall of text.
